content: Badly designed and built app. Some of the games crash or freeze. The reading level is inconsistent - which is bad. Audio and pronunciation are poor. In some cases letter names are used instead of letter sounds. The range of games is limited. The letter tracing doesn't work on a Samsung S9+. This is nowhere near as good as the free apps. Please refund, thankyou.

Games are good but they are so repetitive that kids get bored and don't benefit from the games. There is an extreme lack of variety and imagination that went in this. It could have been much better if just a few more learning modules were added.

A Worthwhile investment. Just downloaded it for my son who is 4 years old . I love the reward system very unique . And it gets progressively harder. But helps the child adjust and learn . And gives hints after child has difficulty. But not to soon let's the trail and error aspect help learning. My son loves the music. Educational and fun . I like how it has no pointless games. Unlike many other apps
My kids love this app even my 3year olds gets in on the action. Definitely makes learning fun especially for kids that have trouble concentrating.

The best learning app for children that we have used. A good range of different activities that use different input mechanisms, and blend letter names and sounds, in a way that works really well for my 3y olds. Try THUP Monkey Math School Sunshine too, it's also better than any other we've found for math!
seth.Lamprecht

My grandson who is 6yrs old and autistic loves this app. Lots of giggles 
and smiles while playing. For sure worth purchasing!!!
Love it
Stopped working after 10 minutes on galaxy tab4. Looked like a good game but we will never know
replyContent:
Sorry for the trouble! If you could email support@thup.com we can help you resolve the problem (and/or provide a refund).  It should work on the Tab4, so just need some more details to provide a fix.

Best,
Thup Games

content: Broken on Galaxy S8 today, image partially off the screen on the left, not registering touch at the right point. Very frustrating.
replyContent:
Sorry for the trouble!  We have been working this week to resolve the issues with the Samsung Galaxy S8 / super wide aspect ratio devices.   If you still have this issue with the latest release (*just* released), please email support@thup.com.  Apologies.

EDIT: Update has been released today along with other improvements.  Thanks for your patience

It should have phonetically sounded spelling for all words instead of using capital letters. It's much easier for children to learn this way. Also, being able to choose the game you want to play as opposed to getting what you're given would be good.

My niece started off with Preschool lunchbox. Now that she is starting to learn her letters and words, I got Word School, and she loves it. So I also purchased Monkey Math. Thanks for a great app!
Fun app for learning. My girls love it, I love it.

Like all of the monkey apps it is engaging for the kids... I can only say 3 stars because when there are letter sounds there are 'uhs' after them, which is not good educationally. Some word sounds, such as using "am" and 'an' and then saying each sound seperately are also not appropriate. When there is spelling I would love to hear letter sounds not letter names as the kids touch each letter and then it reads it back to you. It would be nice if you could increase and decrease the speed of the sight word and letter matching as the words fly by. The word rhyming (make a path) is visually overwhelming. It also goes to the loading screen too often (monkey stone with light that goes around it). Overall it is fun for my kids, but I dont think it is as good as the other mokey apps.
THUP games are really well designed and kid friendly games. No pop-up, simple menu, no in game upgrades or buys. They are educational and fun. As a parent I highly recommended any of their games

Of all the educational apps I have, my 5 yr old daughter loves this the most. I don't know why, but this entertains her for the longest, and keeps her the most engaged. I will say though, that more content would make it even better. Bring on an update that adds new games/features.

This app is great.  My autistic 4.5yo son loves it.  His reading, spelling, and fine motor skills have all improved since we began using it.  As a parent, I really appreciate the design of the settings and support buttons.  Great job with the development and testing of this app.  It looks sharp, transitions are smooth, and we have not experienced any crashes or glitches.  I hope to see more games from THUP very soon!
My 5yr old loves this game, but it frustrates her after a minute into the games it freezes. FIX IT NOW

Our son loves this app.  He likes that it switches through multiple activities instead of repeating the same one over and over.    It seems to progress in difficulty as tasks are completed.  I like that the level can be set to the desired difficulty or the activity removed completely.    I was hesitant to download it without being able to try it out first, but I'm glad I did.  It's an awesome app.  I hope they come out with other apps for math and logic.    I do wish we could turn off the hints.  The hints kick in a little too fast.  There are several times where our son was sounding out a word and just as he found the answer, the game gives it to him.  It looks and works great on our Toshiba Excite 10.

my 5 year old is behind on reading due to hearing problems he gets realy angry with reading and dnt want to do it this game he loves there is a reward system even if they dnt do the best it switches to diffrent little games quickly so keeps him interested downloaded and runs good on samsung galaxy 2 i would say to all get it so much better than traditional flash cards boring they dnt help with kids who dnt have interest this is great finaly a educational game my child will do without anger
